Today I have removed the proxy boilerplate...example below... So the proxy stuff is implicit in environment variables or in a few places CLI parameters. See my latest PR 
https://github.com/hyperledger/sawtooth-seth/pull/95/

Example
```
if [ ! -z $HTTP_PROXY ] && [ -z $http_proxy ]; then \ http_proxy=$HTTP_PROXY; \ fi; \ if [ ! -z $HTTPS_PROXY ] && [ -z $https_proxy ]; then \ https_proxy=$HTTPS_PROXY; \ fi
```
